1
00:00:02.920 --> 00:00:07.090 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Janeway] <i>Captain's Log,</i>
<i>Stardate 54208.3.</i>

2
00:00:07.174 --> 00:00:10.344 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Last month's datastream</i>
<i>from Starfleet never arrived,</i>

3
00:00:10.427 --> 00:00:12.095 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>so the crew is looking</i>
<i>forward to this one</i>

4
00:00:12.179 --> 00:00:14.348 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>with even more anticipation</i>
<i>than usual.</i>

5
00:00:14.431 --> 00:00:16.725 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We could all use</i>
<i>some news from home.</i>

6
00:00:19.019 --> 00:00:22.523 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Ah. There he is,
the man of the hour.

7
00:00:22.606 --> 00:00:24.107 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You sure are in a good mood.

8
00:00:24.191 --> 00:00:27.653 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, rumor has it you snared
the latest datastream last night.

9
00:00:27.736 --> 00:00:30.614 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Technically, it was this morning--
0200 to be exact.

10
00:00:30.697 --> 00:00:33.909 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- So where's my mail?
- Hmm?

11
00:00:33.992 --> 00:00:35.911 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh. Don't tell me
you lost another one.

12
00:00:35.994 --> 00:00:38.038 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I didn't lose
last month's datastream.

13
00:00:38.121 --> 00:00:39.289 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It never arrived.

14
00:00:39.373 --> 00:00:40.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- So what's the holdup this time?
- [sighs]

15
00:00:41.041 --> 00:00:43.752 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The transmission was
a little larger than usual.

16
00:00:43.835 --> 00:00:45.003 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's jammed the transceiver.

17
00:00:45.087 --> 00:00:48.006 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Seven and I have been up
all night trying to download it.

18
00:00:48.090 --> 00:00:49.174 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Harry...

19
00:00:49.258 --> 00:00:51.093 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we can't go another month
without mail.

20
00:00:52.135 --> 00:00:53.845 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, you won't. Trust me.

21
00:00:55.389 --> 00:00:57.015 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sarcastic chuckle]

22
00:01:00.060 --> 00:01:01.103 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Any luck?

23
00:01:01.186 --> 00:01:03.772 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've determined why
we've been having difficulties.

24
00:01:05.065 --> 00:01:07.192 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeping]

25
00:01:07.276 --> 00:01:09.027 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A hologram.

26
00:01:10.112 --> 00:01:13.490 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The transceiver wasn't designed
to store photonic data.

27
00:01:13.574 --> 00:01:16.368 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We have to get it out of there
before it degrades.

28
00:01:16.994 --> 00:01:18.620 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are you doing?

29
00:01:18.704 --> 00:01:21.123 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Tying the transceiver into
the holodeck's pattern buffer.

30
00:01:21.206 --> 00:01:24.167 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Those systems aren't compatible.
You'll depolarize the relays.

31
00:01:24.918 --> 00:01:27.754 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Starfleet wouldn't have sent
this hologram if it weren't important.

32
00:01:27.838 --> 00:01:30.132 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm sure it's worth
a few burnt-out relays.

33
00:01:30.215 --> 00:01:32.342 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[electricity snaps]
[alerts bleeping]

34
00:01:34.052 --> 00:01:35.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You've overloaded
the transceiver.

35
00:01:36.513 --> 00:01:38.682 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But I saved the hologram.

36
00:01:42.101 --> 00:01:44.438 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Okay, ready when you are.

37
00:01:49.901 --> 00:01:51.028 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lieutenant Barclay?

38
00:01:51.111 --> 00:01:53.447 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh, no, but he did design me.

39
00:01:53.530 --> 00:01:56.199 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm a walking, talking,
problem-solving interactive hologram.

40
00:01:56.283 --> 00:01:58.327 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You can call me Reg.

41
00:01:58.410 --> 00:02:00.203 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's nice to meet you, Reg.

42
00:02:00.287 --> 00:02:01.872 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The pleasure's mine, Captain.

43
00:02:01.955 --> 00:02:03.665 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Harry, Seven...

44
00:02:03.749 --> 00:02:05.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've been looking forward
to working with you.

45
00:02:05.584 --> 00:02:06.793 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- You have?
- I know--

46
00:02:06.877 --> 00:02:09.296 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You were expecting letters
from your friends and families.

47
00:02:09.379 --> 00:02:11.715 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But with any luck,
in a few days,

48
00:02:11.798 --> 00:02:15.344 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you'll be seeing them
face-to-face.

49
00:04:04.202 --> 00:04:05.704 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
In three days' time,

50
00:04:05.787 --> 00:04:09.082 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Voyager is going to be
passing through Grid 898--

51
00:04:09.166 --> 00:04:12.669 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
a sector of space occupied
by a red giant star.

52
00:04:12.753 --> 00:04:14.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Sensors detected it
a few days ago.

53
00:04:14.629 --> 00:04:16.798 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
At this very moment,
a team of Federation scientists

54
00:04:16.882 --> 00:04:19.843 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
is orbiting another red giant
in the Alpha Quadrant.

55
00:04:19.926 --> 00:04:24.181 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
In 72 hours, they will target
its magnetic field

56
00:04:24.264 --> 00:04:29.102 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
with a verteron beam,
creating a geodesic fold.

57
00:04:29.186 --> 00:04:31.855 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
As a result,
a corresponding fold will open here

58
00:04:31.938 --> 00:04:35.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
in the magnetic field of the red giant
that Voyager is approaching.

59
00:04:35.609 --> 00:04:39.446 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Space will be punctured...
these two points

60
00:04:39.529 --> 00:04:43.033 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
creating a gateway
between the quadrants.

61
00:04:43.116 --> 00:04:46.203 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Our shields are useless
against geodesic radiation.

62
00:04:46.286 --> 00:04:49.206 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
We toyed with the idea
of opening a fold ourselves,

63
00:04:49.289 --> 00:04:51.917 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
but it didn't take us long to realize
we wouldn't survive the trip.

64
00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:55.629 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
A lot's happened in geodesic research
since you've been gone.

65
00:04:55.712 --> 00:04:57.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I've brought schematics
for shield upgrades

66
00:04:57.464 --> 00:04:59.758 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
to deflect the radiation
from the fold,

67
00:04:59.841 --> 00:05:02.969 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
medical technology to provide
additional protection for the crew.

68
00:05:03.053 --> 00:05:04.262 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We've thought of everything.

69
00:05:04.346 --> 00:05:07.432 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Starfleet never mentioned you
in any of the previous datastreams.

70
00:05:07.516 --> 00:05:10.477 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Well, Lieutenant Barclay
didn't want to raise your hopes,

71
00:05:10.560 --> 00:05:12.646 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
in case the plan
didn't live up to expectation,

72
00:05:12.729 --> 00:05:14.773 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
but lucky for you,
it surpassed them.

73
00:05:14.856 --> 00:05:16.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
What about
last month's datastream?

74
00:05:16.983 --> 00:05:18.527 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Why didn't we receive it?

75
00:05:18.610 --> 00:05:22.364 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Pathfinder tried sending
an unabridged version of my program.

76
00:05:22.447 --> 00:05:23.782 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
It overloaded the MIDAS Array.

77
00:05:23.865 --> 00:05:26.368 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And the only casualty this time
was our transceiver.

78
00:05:26.451 --> 00:05:29.079 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
If everything goes according to plan,
you won't need it anymore.

79
00:05:31.498 --> 00:05:34.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
If we were to attempt this,

80
00:05:34.084 --> 00:05:36.378 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
you'd need access
to areas of this ship

81
00:05:36.461 --> 00:05:38.296 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
that aren't equipped
with holo-emitters.

82
00:05:38.380 --> 00:05:42.968 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Not to worry, Captain.
We've thought of that, too.

83
00:05:43.051 --> 00:05:45.679 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
My emitter is your emitter.

84
00:05:46.930 --> 00:05:50.141 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Computer, transfer the Barclay
hologram to the mobile emitter.

85
00:05:50.225 --> 00:05:52.936 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- [beeping]
- [Computer] Transfer complete.

86
00:05:53.019 --> 00:05:55.981 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
On Lieutenant Barclay's
behalf, I thank you.

87
00:05:56.064 --> 00:05:58.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just make sure to return it
when we get to Earth. [chuckling]

88
00:05:58.984 --> 00:06:01.194 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Chakotay] We're ready for you
in the briefing room, Captain.

89
00:06:01.778 --> 00:06:03.238 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Excuse us, Doctor.

90
00:06:04.239 --> 00:06:06.867 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
I'm sure you have a full day planned,
but if you have time,

91
00:06:06.950 --> 00:06:08.367 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'd like to get
better acquainted.

92
00:06:08.451 --> 00:06:10.704 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll stop by
the first chance I get.

93
00:06:10.787 --> 00:06:11.913 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You'll know where to find me.

94
00:06:11.997 --> 00:06:15.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is our destination--
Red Giant 23139.

95
00:06:15.834 --> 00:06:18.461 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The geodesic fold
will open here,

96
00:06:18.545 --> 00:06:20.297 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
adjacent to the giant's
northern pole.

97
00:06:20.379 --> 00:06:24.134 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We'll have exactly 16 seconds
to take Voyager through.

98
00:06:24.217 --> 00:06:25.927 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Reg has prepared
a list of assignments.

99
00:06:26.011 --> 00:06:28.387 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I expect you to give him
your full cooperation.

100
00:06:28.471 --> 00:06:31.558 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Mr. Paris, you have the honor
of plotting our course to Big Red 2.

101
00:06:31.641 --> 00:06:33.768 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Lieutenant Torres,
Commander Tuvok,

102
00:06:33.852 --> 00:06:36.563 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'd like you to start working
on shield modifications.

103
00:06:36.646 --> 00:06:38.523 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And in the meantime,
I've asked the Doctor

104
00:06:38.607 --> 00:06:40.066 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to prepare a series
of inoculations

105
00:06:40.150 --> 00:06:42.277 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that will protect the crew
from the radiation.

106
00:06:42.360 --> 00:06:43.778 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We should discuss
the possibility

107
00:06:43.862 --> 00:06:46.405 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
of applying Borg technology
to Starfleet's plan.

108
00:06:46.489 --> 00:06:49.159 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It could increase
our chances of success.

109
00:06:49.242 --> 00:06:51.453 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I look forward to hearing
your thoughts.

110
00:06:51.536 --> 00:06:53.288 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How long before
the transceiver's back on line?

111
00:06:53.371 --> 00:06:54.956 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No more than two hours.

112
00:06:55.040 --> 00:06:57.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then we'll still have time
to transmit a response to Starfleet.

113
00:06:57.751 --> 00:06:59.085 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Keep us posted.

114
00:06:59.169 --> 00:07:00.419 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'd like to send
Lieutenant Barclay

115
00:07:00.503 --> 00:07:02.255 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a little thank-you note
for all his hard work.

116
00:07:03.256 --> 00:07:04.799 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Um, uh, is there...

117
00:07:04.883 --> 00:07:06.384 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
is there anything
I can do, Reg?

118
00:07:06.468 --> 00:07:09.387 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your job might be
the most important one of all.

119
00:07:09.471 --> 00:07:11.097 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The next few days
will be difficult.

120
00:07:11.181 --> 00:07:13.892 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The crew will be working
extremely long hours.

121
00:07:13.975 --> 00:07:15.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They're going to need an
experienced Morale Officer

122
00:07:15.852 --> 00:07:17.103 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to keep their spirits high.

123
00:07:17.187 --> 00:07:18.813 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You can count on me.

124
00:07:20.774 --> 00:07:22.567 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If this were any other ship...

125
00:07:23.985 --> 00:07:26.112 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'd have my doubts.

126
00:07:26.196 --> 00:07:28.782 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But this is Voyager,
"the miracle ship."

127
00:07:29.866 --> 00:07:32.827 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You've survived six years
in the Delta Quadrant.

128
00:07:32.911 --> 00:07:36.706 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You've evaded the Kazon,
the Vidiians, the Hirogen.

129
00:07:36.790 --> 00:07:38.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You've even faced down the Borg.

130
00:07:39.459 --> 00:07:41.419 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think, with a little teamwork,

131
00:07:41.503 --> 00:07:45.090 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we can pull off one more miracle
and take Voyager home.

132
00:07:46.591 --> 00:07:48.635 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can taste
my mom's cooking.

133
00:07:48.718 --> 00:07:51.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don't forget what
the hologram said, Harry:

134
00:07:51.304 --> 00:07:53.974 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- "This is Voyager".
- "The miracle ship"!

135
00:07:54.057 --> 00:07:56.226 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Uh, not when it comes
to getting us home.

136
00:07:56.309 --> 00:07:59.354 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Our shortcuts have a tendency
to blow up in our faces.

137
00:07:59.437 --> 00:08:01.106 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, that's looking
on the bright side.

138
00:08:01.189 --> 00:08:05.443 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, remember Arturis
and his quantum slipstream drive?

139
00:08:05.527 --> 00:08:09.614 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Or, um, or how about
the telepathic pitcher plant

140
00:08:09.698 --> 00:08:11.574 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that made us think
we were on our way home

141
00:08:11.658 --> 00:08:13.243 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
right before it tried
to eat the ship.

142
00:08:13.326 --> 00:08:15.912 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is the best opportunity
we've had.

143
00:08:15.996 --> 00:08:18.373 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yeah, which is why we'll probably
end up in the Gamma Quadrant.

144
00:08:18.456 --> 00:08:20.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll remind you of that
when we get back to Earth.

145
00:08:20.542 --> 00:08:21.918 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't say I didn't warn you.

146
00:08:22.002 --> 00:08:24.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Seven] When a Borg cube
enters a transwarp conduit,

147
00:08:24.629 --> 00:08:26.423 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
it's subject to extreme
gravimetric shear.

148
00:08:27.507 --> 00:08:30.260 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
To compensate, the Borg project
a structural integrity field

149
00:08:30.343 --> 00:08:31.636 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
ahead of the cube.

150
00:08:31.720 --> 00:08:33.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
By modifying
Voyager's deflector,

151
00:08:33.304 --> 00:08:35.181 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we may be able
to do the same.

152
00:08:35.265 --> 00:08:37.726 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No one at Starfleet
would have thought of this.

153
00:08:39.602 --> 00:08:41.688 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So, what's the first thing

154
00:08:41.771 --> 00:08:43.356 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you're going to do
when you get back?

155
00:08:43.440 --> 00:08:45.150 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Begin repairs to Voyager.

156
00:08:45.233 --> 00:08:47.027 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Even with the structural
integrity field,

157
00:08:47.110 --> 00:08:49.446 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
it's likely the ship
will suffer significant damage.

158
00:08:49.529 --> 00:08:52.449 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yes, but, I mean, there are
people at Utopia Planitia

159
00:08:52.532 --> 00:08:53.867 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
who will take care of that.

160
00:08:53.950 --> 00:08:55.285 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There are engineering crews
and technicians...

161
00:08:55.368 --> 00:08:57.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are you implying that
I am superfluous?

162
00:08:57.537 --> 00:08:58.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of course not.

163
00:08:59.039 --> 00:09:01.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I only meant that if
you're too busy working,

164
00:09:01.374 --> 00:09:04.669 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you're going to miss all
the "welcome home" hoopla.

165
00:09:05.462 --> 00:09:07.297 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Starfleet's planning parties.

166
00:09:07.380 --> 00:09:08.715 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They'll have ceremonies
and speeches.

167
00:09:08.798 --> 00:09:12.677 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There, there's a ticker-tape
parade down Market Street.

168
00:09:12.761 --> 00:09:14.763 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I won't be attending
any of those events.

169
00:09:14.846 --> 00:09:17.932 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But you'd be
the guest of honor.

170
00:09:19.642 --> 00:09:21.978 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When I first arrived
on Voyager,

171
00:09:22.062 --> 00:09:25.315 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
it was difficult
for the crew to accept me.

172
00:09:25.398 --> 00:09:27.484 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm anticipating
a similar welcome on Earth.

173
00:09:28.860 --> 00:09:34.532 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You don't have
any idea, do you?

174
00:09:36.201 --> 00:09:37.744 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I didn't mention this earlier.

175
00:09:37.827 --> 00:09:39.954 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I didn't want to hurt
anybody's feelings...

176
00:09:40.038 --> 00:09:41.206 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but you are the one

177
00:09:41.289 --> 00:09:44.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
who people are most
looking forward to seeing.

178
00:09:44.084 --> 00:09:45.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's difficult to believe.

179
00:09:45.960 --> 00:09:48.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- Why?
- I was Borg.

180
00:09:48.421 --> 00:09:49.756 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Exactly.

181
00:09:49.839 --> 00:09:53.009 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You <i>were </i>Borg,
but you escaped.

182
00:09:53.093 --> 00:09:55.011 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And despite incredible odds,

183
00:09:55.095 --> 00:09:58.098 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you managed to reclaim
your humanity.

184
00:09:58.181 --> 00:10:00.683 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No one's ever done that before.
You're famous.

185
00:10:01.392 --> 00:10:02.936 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Fame is irrelevant.

186
00:10:03.019 --> 00:10:04.896 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe...

187
00:10:04.979 --> 00:10:06.523 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but you've given hope

188
00:10:06.606 --> 00:10:09.150 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to everyone who's ever
lost somebody to the Borg.

189
00:10:11.194 --> 00:10:13.530 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You've inspired millions.

190
00:10:17.617 --> 00:10:20.620 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you think my participation
in the "hoopla"

191
00:10:20.703 --> 00:10:24.207 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
would be beneficial to others,
then I'll comply.

192
00:10:38.346 --> 00:10:40.515 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Is this going to take
much longer, Reg?

193
00:10:40.598 --> 00:10:42.851 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, the computer
is still inputting data.

194
00:10:43.560 --> 00:10:44.936 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That should do it.

195
00:10:45.979 --> 00:10:49.315 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All right. Computer,
display the intended trajectory

196
00:10:49.399 --> 00:10:51.734 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
of the datastream transmitted
at 0600 this morning.

197
00:10:55.738 --> 00:10:59.659 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, display the actual trajectory
and identify the termination point.

198
00:10:59.742 --> 00:11:02.829 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Computer] <i>The trajectory</i>
<i>ends in Sector 395...</i>

199
00:11:02.912 --> 00:11:04.497 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
42, Grid 8.

200
00:11:04.581 --> 00:11:06.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[sighs]
Does that sound familiar?

201
00:11:07.000 --> 00:11:09.586 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's exactly where the datastream
dissipated last month.

202
00:11:10.211 --> 00:11:12.005 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There <i>is </i>something there.

203
00:11:12.088 --> 00:11:15.592 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There is something preventing
the datastream from reaching Voyager.

204
00:11:15.674 --> 00:11:18.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Uh, a micro-wormhole,
a radiogenic field...

205
00:11:18.553 --> 00:11:21.181 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Long-range scans
didn't pick up anything unusual.

206
00:11:21.264 --> 00:11:25.351 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, still, we could send
a ship to investigate.

207
00:11:25.435 --> 00:11:26.811 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We could confirm my theory.

208
00:11:26.895 --> 00:11:28.605 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What about <i>my </i>theory, Reg?

209
00:11:28.687 --> 00:11:30.899 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The hologram
was too complex.

210
00:11:30.982 --> 00:11:32.650 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It caused the data streams
to degrade

211
00:11:32.734 --> 00:11:34.485 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
before they reached
their destination.

212
00:11:35.028 --> 00:11:36.154 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, to be honest,

213
00:11:36.237 --> 00:11:39.741 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I... I don't agree.

214
00:11:39.824 --> 00:11:43.203 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The truth is, we don't know
what happened to my hologram.

215
00:11:43.286 --> 00:11:45.788 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then let's stick
to what we do know.

216
00:11:45.872 --> 00:11:47.665 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
For the second month
in a row,

217
00:11:47.749 --> 00:11:49.834 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we tried sending
your hologram to Voyager.

218
00:11:49.918 --> 00:11:52.337 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And for the second month
in a row, it failed to get there.

219
00:11:52.420 --> 00:11:54.422 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And I want to know why,
so it doesn't happen a third time.

220
00:11:55.465 --> 00:11:57.050 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It won't happen a third time.

221
00:11:58.676 --> 00:12:01.429 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Next month, we go back
to standard transmissions.

222
00:12:01.512 --> 00:12:04.057 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But a holographic matrix
carries twice the information,

223
00:12:04.140 --> 00:12:05.433 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
interact with the crew...

224
00:12:05.516 --> 00:12:08.019 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Admiral Paris wants us
to send more practical data,

225
00:12:08.102 --> 00:12:10.688 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
like tactical upgrades,
letters from the crew's families.

226
00:12:10.772 --> 00:12:11.814 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But, Pete...

227
00:12:11.898 --> 00:12:14.733 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sending a hologram to Voyager
was a good idea,

228
00:12:14.817 --> 00:12:16.361 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but it didn't work.

229
00:12:16.444 --> 00:12:19.030 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's time to move on.

230
00:12:26.329 --> 00:12:29.082 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And this is
the research lab,

231
00:12:29.165 --> 00:12:32.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
where most of Pathfinder's
homework gets done.

232
00:12:32.961 --> 00:12:35.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All the datastreams
are compressed here

233
00:12:35.421 --> 00:12:38.925 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and then transmitted all the way
to the Delta Quadrant.

234
00:12:39.008 --> 00:12:40.677 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your teacher tells me
you've been studying

235
00:12:40.759 --> 00:12:42.262 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
some of the Delta
Quadrant races

236
00:12:42.345 --> 00:12:44.180 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that Voyager
has described to us.

237
00:12:44.264 --> 00:12:45.682 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who can name one for me?

238
00:12:45.764 --> 00:12:47.267 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The Talaxians.

239
00:12:47.350 --> 00:12:48.393 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Very good.

240
00:12:48.601 --> 00:12:49.644 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The Ocampa.

241
00:12:49.727 --> 00:12:50.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's right. Who else?

242
00:12:50.895 --> 00:12:53.356 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Barclay]
The Borg! The Borg!

243
00:12:53.439 --> 00:12:55.817 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They assimilated my hologram.
That's how it disappeared.

244
00:12:55.900 --> 00:12:57.026 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Reg, now isn't the time.

245
00:12:57.110 --> 00:12:58.528 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Look at this-- last month,

246
00:12:58.611 --> 00:13:01.447 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a spacecraft passed within 20 meters
of the MIDAS Array,

247
00:13:01.531 --> 00:13:03.408 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
just hours before
we sent the first hologram.

248
00:13:03.491 --> 00:13:05.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- What is your point?
- 20 meters.

249
00:13:05.827 --> 00:13:07.412 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's awfully close,
don't you think?

250
00:13:07.495 --> 00:13:09.163 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- Ensign--
- Look, the Borg must have sent

251
00:13:09.247 --> 00:13:11.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a transwarp probe
to steal my hologram.

252
00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:15.086 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe because they-- they thought
that it was carrying

253
00:13:15.169 --> 00:13:17.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
anti-Borg technology
to Voyager.

254
00:13:17.422 --> 00:13:19.299 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It wasn't the Borg, Reg.

255
00:13:19.382 --> 00:13:21.634 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then it was the Romulans
using a cloaked ship.

256
00:13:21.718 --> 00:13:23.636 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They've been curious
about Voyager for years...

257
00:13:23.720 --> 00:13:24.929 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- That is enough.
- But, you...

258
00:13:25.013 --> 00:13:28.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I am sorry your idea
didn't work,

259
00:13:28.433 --> 00:13:30.184 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I can't have you
going off on a tangent.

260
00:13:30.268 --> 00:13:31.894 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not again.

261
00:13:31.978 --> 00:13:34.897 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You'll be no good
to Pathfinder or Voyager.

262
00:13:37.150 --> 00:13:39.569 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How much leave
do you have saved up?

263
00:13:40.819 --> 00:13:42.530 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not that much.

264
00:13:42.613 --> 00:13:44.949 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
50... maybe 60 days.

265
00:13:45.033 --> 00:13:47.368 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Take a week, go home.
Try to relax.

266
00:13:47.452 --> 00:13:49.329 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- But, Pete...
- No.

267
00:13:49.412 --> 00:13:51.372 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That was not a request, Lieutenant.

268
00:13:56.169 --> 00:13:58.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe I'll go somewhere...

269
00:14:01.215 --> 00:14:02.258 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
take a vacation.

270
00:14:03.509 --> 00:14:07.096 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now that is the most sensible thing
I've heard you say all day.

271
00:14:08.139 --> 00:14:10.683 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
My cousin has
a beach house in Malaysia.

272
00:14:10.767 --> 00:14:12.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She'd be happy
to lend it to you.

273
00:14:14.395 --> 00:14:19.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Thanks, um, but I have
someplace else in mind.

274
00:14:28.868 --> 00:14:30.036 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You, you wanted to see me?

275
00:14:30.119 --> 00:14:33.122 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've been going over
the instructions from Starfleet Medical.

276
00:14:33.206 --> 00:14:37.585 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
As far as I can tell, their "new"
inoculations aren't much different

277
00:14:37.668 --> 00:14:40.088 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
from run-of-the-mill
radiogenic vaccines.

278
00:14:40.171 --> 00:14:42.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't think
they'll protect the crew.

279
00:14:42.382 --> 00:14:44.550 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Did you try incorporating
a synthetic antigen?

280
00:14:44.634 --> 00:14:48.054 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yes, but it only improved
the resistance by 10 percent.

281
00:14:48.137 --> 00:14:49.514 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That should be enough.

282
00:14:49.597 --> 00:14:53.101 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[sighs] We can't afford
to be cavalier, Reg.

283
00:14:53.184 --> 00:14:57.105 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If these treatments don't work,
the crew will wind up liquefied.

284
00:14:57.188 --> 00:14:58.940 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're forgetting
that the inoculations

285
00:14:59.023 --> 00:15:00.358 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
aren't designed
to work alone.

286
00:15:00.441 --> 00:15:02.193 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They were intended to work
in combination

287
00:15:02.276 --> 00:15:03.903 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
with the shield modifications.

288
00:15:03.986 --> 00:15:06.572 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's the medicinal "ying"
to the shields' "yang."

289
00:15:06.656 --> 00:15:09.742 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A-and what if the "yang"
doesn't work?

290
00:15:09.826 --> 00:15:11.285 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's not going to happen.

291
00:15:11.369 --> 00:15:15.998 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, listen, Lieutenant Barclay
has a special affinity for this crew.

292
00:15:16.082 --> 00:15:17.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So do I.

293
00:15:17.208 --> 00:15:20.002 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I promise you,
we won't let them down.

294
00:15:21.087 --> 00:15:22.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of course you won't.

295
00:15:22.755 --> 00:15:23.798 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Tell me...

296
00:15:24.674 --> 00:15:27.218 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
do you also share
Lieutenant Barclay's affinity for golf?

297
00:15:27.301 --> 00:15:28.511 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughs]

298
00:15:28.594 --> 00:15:30.138 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We have identical handicaps.

299
00:15:30.221 --> 00:15:32.181 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, if you're not busy later,

300
00:15:32.265 --> 00:15:34.392 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
perhaps we could play nine holes
on the holodeck.

301
00:15:34.475 --> 00:15:36.602 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Eh, it's tempting, but I still have

302
00:15:36.686 --> 00:15:38.521 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
a few dozen
progress reports to look over.

303
00:15:38.604 --> 00:15:40.064 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, in that case,

304
00:15:40.148 --> 00:15:41.816 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
maybe you could
look over them here,

305
00:15:41.899 --> 00:15:44.527 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so that I could borrow
the mobile emitter.

306
00:15:44.610 --> 00:15:47.196 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Providing that the rest
of the day's work goes smoothly,

307
00:15:47.280 --> 00:15:49.198 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- consider it yours.
- I...

308
00:15:51.701 --> 00:15:53.619 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I thought it <i>was </i>mine.

309
00:15:55.538 --> 00:15:56.956 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Commander Chakotay tells me

310
00:15:57.039 --> 00:15:59.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that you finished
repairing the transceiver.

311
00:15:59.167 --> 00:16:02.336 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We were just about to send
the Captain's reply to Lieutenant Barclay.

312
00:16:02.420 --> 00:16:05.089 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you have enough room
to include a progress report from me?

313
00:16:05.173 --> 00:16:07.091 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think we can squeeze that in.

314
00:16:08.968 --> 00:16:13.806 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Computer, download Barclay Hologram
File 01 to the data block.

315
00:16:14.807 --> 00:16:16.184 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Computer]
<i>Download complete.</i>

316
00:16:17.185 --> 00:16:18.936 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Transmitting.

317
00:16:44.504 --> 00:16:46.339 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeping]

318
00:16:47.840 --> 00:16:49.926 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's about time.

319
00:16:50.009 --> 00:16:52.470 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Janeway] <i>Greetings from</i>
<i>the Delta Quadrant, Lieutenant.</i>

320
00:16:52.553 --> 00:16:55.389 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You'll be happy to know that
your hologram reached us safely...

321
00:16:55.473 --> 00:16:57.558 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Get to the important part.

322
00:17:01.145 --> 00:17:03.356 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In accordance with the
74th Rule of Acquisition,

323
00:17:03.439 --> 00:17:04.815 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Knowledge Equals Profit",

324
00:17:04.899 --> 00:17:07.902 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've enclosed the specifications
you've requested.

325
00:17:07.985 --> 00:17:09.028 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
See you soon.

326
00:17:10.238 --> 00:17:12.907 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, look at those hands.

327
00:17:12.990 --> 00:17:14.784 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I bet she gives great oo-mox.

328
00:17:14.867 --> 00:17:17.495 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Too bad she'll be dead
when she gets here.

329
00:17:17.578 --> 00:17:19.705 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Forget the hands.

330
00:17:19.789 --> 00:17:21.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Show me the nanoprobes.

331
00:17:25.002 --> 00:17:26.837 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How many are there?

332
00:17:26.921 --> 00:17:28.464 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
3.6 million.

333
00:17:28.548 --> 00:17:31.634 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's 20 percent more
than we predicted.

334
00:17:31.717 --> 00:17:35.721 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
3.6 million nanoprobes
at six bars of latinum per unit.

335
00:17:35.805 --> 00:17:37.223 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh, that comes to...

336
00:17:37.306 --> 00:17:40.810 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
More profit than
we ever dreamed of.

337
00:17:40.893 --> 00:17:44.063 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[all laughing]

338
00:17:53.406 --> 00:17:55.533 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughing and conversing]

339
00:18:05.710 --> 00:18:06.752 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Your drink, sir.

340
00:18:07.587 --> 00:18:08.754 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you.

341
00:18:09.422 --> 00:18:10.840 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you.

342
00:18:19.348 --> 00:18:20.558 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Something to drink,
ma'am?

343
00:18:21.642 --> 00:18:23.811 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- I'm fine, thanks.
- Are you sure?

344
00:18:23.894 --> 00:18:27.231 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've got a chocolate passion punch
with your name on it.

345
00:18:27.315 --> 00:18:28.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughing]

346
00:18:28.482 --> 00:18:29.358 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Reg?

347
00:18:29.859 --> 00:18:30.985 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Surprise.

348
00:18:33.654 --> 00:18:34.822 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where's Commander Riker?

349
00:18:34.905 --> 00:18:38.284 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- He doesn't arrive until Friday.
- Oh.

350
00:18:38.367 --> 00:18:40.161 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The question is,
what are you doing here?

351
00:18:40.244 --> 00:18:41.996 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Just had some time off.

352
00:18:42.079 --> 00:18:44.749 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your letter made this place
sound fun,

353
00:18:44.832 --> 00:18:47.001 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and just thought I'd join you.

354
00:18:47.084 --> 00:18:50.212 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you have any idea
how inappropriate it is

355
00:18:50.296 --> 00:18:52.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to follow your therapist
on vacation?

356
00:18:52.882 --> 00:18:54.300 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Please.

357
00:18:54.383 --> 00:18:55.593 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They might be watching.

358
00:18:56.594 --> 00:18:57.428 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who?

359
00:18:58.346 --> 00:19:01.515 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Borg, the Romulans.
I'm not sure yet.

360
00:19:01.599 --> 00:19:03.309 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Please...

361
00:19:04.060 --> 00:19:06.646 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Deanna, I need your help.

362
00:19:08.981 --> 00:19:11.192 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Commander Harkins is usually
willing to hear me out,

363
00:19:11.275 --> 00:19:13.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but this time, he wouldn't even
look at my evidence.

364
00:19:13.319 --> 00:19:17.239 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm not sure any of this
qualifies as evidence, Reg.

365
00:19:17.323 --> 00:19:18.824 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You don't believe me, either.

366
00:19:18.908 --> 00:19:20.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You think I'm imagining this?

367
00:19:21.452 --> 00:19:22.953 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Just like Pete?

368
00:19:24.330 --> 00:19:29.335 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The last time I saw you,
you were laughing, telling jokes.

369
00:19:30.169 --> 00:19:32.129 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You even sang a duet
with Data.

370
00:19:32.213 --> 00:19:33.714 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughing]

371
00:19:33.798 --> 00:19:36.050 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That was Commander La Forge's
birthday party.

372
00:19:37.301 --> 00:19:39.720 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You were a completely
different Reg that night.

373
00:19:39.804 --> 00:19:42.390 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh... things were better then.

374
00:19:42.473 --> 00:19:44.392 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- How?
- Well, for one thing

375
00:19:44.475 --> 00:19:46.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I had just finished the matrix
for my hologram,

376
00:19:46.852 --> 00:19:49.772 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and I showed Geordi
some of the specs that night.

377
00:19:49.855 --> 00:19:51.691 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He said he was proud of me.

378
00:19:51.774 --> 00:19:52.817 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What else?

379
00:19:53.609 --> 00:19:57.738 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh... the Dragons
had just won the pennant,

380
00:19:57.822 --> 00:20:01.992 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and I was still seeing Leosa.

381
00:20:02.076 --> 00:20:03.953 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You mentioned her at the party.

382
00:20:04.036 --> 00:20:05.079 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A teacher, right?

383
00:20:05.913 --> 00:20:10.626 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Everything was going so well--
my job, my personal life.

384
00:20:11.669 --> 00:20:14.714 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I started to think
maybe my luck was changing.

385
00:20:15.631 --> 00:20:18.676 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- And then you lost your hologram.
- [yells]

386
00:20:22.012 --> 00:20:23.931 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Admiral Paris was furious.

387
00:20:24.014 --> 00:20:27.268 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He said we'd-- we'd wasted
a transmission to Voyager.

388
00:20:27.351 --> 00:20:29.437 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Pete talked him into
giving us another chance,

389
00:20:29.520 --> 00:20:31.439 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but there was so much
pressure after that.

390
00:20:31.522 --> 00:20:33.899 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Did it put a strain
on your relationship with Leosa?

391
00:20:33.983 --> 00:20:36.026 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- She left me.
- Oh, I'm sorry.

392
00:20:36.110 --> 00:20:38.237 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I went to her apartment.
She was gone.

393
00:20:38.320 --> 00:20:40.531 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There was no furniture,
no forwarding address,

394
00:20:40.614 --> 00:20:42.700 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
not even a "Dear Reg" letter.

395
00:20:42.783 --> 00:20:44.577 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That must have been
very upsetting.

396
00:20:44.660 --> 00:20:46.579 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Mmm.
It's just my luck, right?

397
00:20:46.662 --> 00:20:48.789 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Lose the hologram
and the girl.

398
00:20:49.999 --> 00:20:51.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Troi]
Tell me more about Leosa.

399
00:20:51.751 --> 00:20:53.627 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh. You would have
liked her.

400
00:20:53.711 --> 00:20:56.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She was sweet,
she was thoughtful

401
00:20:56.756 --> 00:20:59.508 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and such
a wonderful listener.

402
00:20:59.592 --> 00:21:01.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She would let me--
let me go on for hours.

403
00:21:01.552 --> 00:21:02.595 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

404
00:21:02.678 --> 00:21:04.180 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What did you talk about?

405
00:21:04.263 --> 00:21:08.225 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh. She was fascinated
by my work at Pathfinder

406
00:21:08.309 --> 00:21:09.351 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and, uh...

407
00:21:10.686 --> 00:21:12.813 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
she didn't, uh...

408
00:21:14.023 --> 00:21:16.108 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
she didn't find
any of it boring.

409
00:21:17.026 --> 00:21:20.488 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She made me feel...
interesting.

410
00:21:20.571 --> 00:21:24.158 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What do you feel
when we talk about her now?

411
00:21:24.241 --> 00:21:28.871 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Um, sadness, I suppose.

412
00:21:30.206 --> 00:21:31.248 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A little confusion.

413
00:21:32.458 --> 00:21:35.044 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm sensing
something else...

414
00:21:35.127 --> 00:21:37.379 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
something beneath
the surface.

415
00:21:37.463 --> 00:21:38.506 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What?

416
00:21:38.589 --> 00:21:41.342 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think you might be
sensing it, too.

417
00:21:41.425 --> 00:21:42.468 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What?

418
00:21:42.551 --> 00:21:44.261 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Suspicion, Reg.

419
00:21:44.345 --> 00:21:46.514 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You suspect her of something.

420
00:21:46.597 --> 00:21:50.392 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I suspect that she's happier
without me, if that's what you mean.

421
00:21:51.185 --> 00:21:55.147 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You think Leosa had something to do
with your disappearing hologram,

422
00:21:55.231 --> 00:21:57.733 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but you can't bring yourself
to admit it.

423
00:21:57.817 --> 00:22:02.154 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's why you're projecting
your suspicions onto others.

424
00:22:02.238 --> 00:22:03.739 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're in denial.

425
00:22:06.075 --> 00:22:11.163 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If there's any chance Leosa
did breach Pathfinder security,

426
00:22:11.247 --> 00:22:13.040 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you need to tell
your superiors.

427
00:22:13.123 --> 00:22:15.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I-- I'd be humiliated... again.

428
00:22:17.753 --> 00:22:18.921 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll go with you.

429
00:22:19.964 --> 00:22:21.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What about your vacation?

430
00:22:22.424 --> 00:22:24.510 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll be back here
before Will arrives.

431
00:22:25.511 --> 00:22:28.055 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do you really think it's possible

432
00:22:28.138 --> 00:22:32.685 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
that Leosa stole my hologram?

433
00:22:34.061 --> 00:22:36.146 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why would she do that?

434
00:22:37.898 --> 00:22:41.527 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe... maybe she wanted
something to remember me by.

435
00:22:44.321 --> 00:22:46.532 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Janeway]
<i>Captain's Log, supplemental.</i>

436
00:22:46.615 --> 00:22:48.701 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>With the help</i>
<i>of the Barclay hologram,</i>

437
00:22:48.784 --> 00:22:51.745 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>we've nearly completed</i>
<i>the modifications to Voyager.</i>

438
00:22:51.829 --> 00:22:56.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>As for Reg, he's becoming</i>
<i>extremely popular with the crew.</i>

439
00:22:56.584 --> 00:22:58.252 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Janeway's voice]
Imagine my disappointment

440
00:22:58.335 --> 00:23:02.006 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
when I discovered that Lieutenant Paris
had eaten all the scrambled eggs.

441
00:23:02.089 --> 00:23:03.132 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughter]

442
00:23:03.215 --> 00:23:05.801 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It was pure,
unadulterated gluttony,

443
00:23:05.885 --> 00:23:09.013 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
gastronomic conduct
unbecoming a Starfleet officer.

444
00:23:09.096 --> 00:23:12.808 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He knows it's my favorite breakfast,
but he ate them anyway.

445
00:23:12.892 --> 00:23:15.352 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We have an egg-mergency
here, people.

446
00:23:16.437 --> 00:23:19.148 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I want to know
what you plan to do about it.

447
00:23:19.982 --> 00:23:22.693 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe I can replicate
some more, Captain.

448
00:23:23.401 --> 00:23:24.445 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do it.

449
00:23:25.403 --> 00:23:26.447 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[applause and laughter]

450
00:23:27.865 --> 00:23:30.868 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[normal voice] Thank you.
Thank you, thank you, thank you.

451
00:23:32.202 --> 00:23:35.331 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He's not only programmed
to get us home, he does impressions.

452
00:23:35.413 --> 00:23:37.124 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You see, it's always bothered
Lieutenant Barclay

453
00:23:37.207 --> 00:23:38.918 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that he was uncomfortable
in large groups.

454
00:23:39.001 --> 00:23:42.755 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So he designed me
to be the life of the party.

455
00:23:42.838 --> 00:23:44.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughter]

456
00:23:44.381 --> 00:23:45.633 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I hope he's not too shy.

457
00:23:45.716 --> 00:23:47.968 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He's going to have 150 new friends
when we get back home.

458
00:23:48.052 --> 00:23:51.347 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If we get home, Harry, if.

459
00:23:51.429 --> 00:23:52.932 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Pardon my friend here.

460
00:23:53.015 --> 00:23:54.099 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's convinced we're destined

461
00:23:54.183 --> 00:23:56.477 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to live out our days
in the Delta Quadrant.

462
00:23:56.560 --> 00:23:59.146 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Tuvok's voice]
Your pessimism is illogical.

463
00:23:59.229 --> 00:24:02.191 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Perhaps a mind-meld would help
to alleviate your concern.

464
00:24:02.274 --> 00:24:03.484 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughter]

465
00:24:04.442 --> 00:24:05.569 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Doctor]
<i>Sickbay to Reg.</i>

466
00:24:05.653 --> 00:24:07.154 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Please report to Holodeck 2.</i>

467
00:24:07.821 --> 00:24:09.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
On my way.

468
00:24:15.120 --> 00:24:17.957 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was starting to think
you'd forgotten our tee time.

469
00:24:18.040 --> 00:24:20.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So, what'll it be?

470
00:24:20.376 --> 00:24:23.796 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Pebble Beach at sunset?
The back nine at Gedi Prime?

471
00:24:23.879 --> 00:24:24.922 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Actually, Doctor...

472
00:24:26.340 --> 00:24:27.424 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm afraid
something's come up.

473
00:24:27.508 --> 00:24:29.176 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm going to meet
with Seven of Nine.

474
00:24:29.259 --> 00:24:30.386 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, really?

475
00:24:30.468 --> 00:24:32.888 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She's going to teach me
to play Kadis-Kot.

476
00:24:32.972 --> 00:24:34.765 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh, Reg...

477
00:24:34.848 --> 00:24:36.392 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
when I agreed
to lend you my emitter,

478
00:24:36.474 --> 00:24:39.228 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I did it with the understanding
that you needed it for official business.

479
00:24:39.311 --> 00:24:40.604 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's your point?

480
00:24:41.438 --> 00:24:44.692 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
My point is that board games
aren't exactly crucial to your mission.

481
00:24:44.775 --> 00:24:47.861 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And I suppose golf is?

482
00:24:48.737 --> 00:24:50.364 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Reg...

483
00:24:53.491 --> 00:24:55.202 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll tell you what.

484
00:24:55.285 --> 00:24:56.870 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
When we get back home,

485
00:24:56.954 --> 00:24:58.956 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we'll play as much golf
as you like.

486
00:24:59.039 --> 00:25:02.418 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Until then, let's try to keep out
of each other's hair.

487
00:25:03.168 --> 00:25:04.336 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What do you say?

488
00:25:11.677 --> 00:25:13.220 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Admiral Paris]
State your name for the record.

489
00:25:14.805 --> 00:25:16.265 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Leosa.

490
00:25:16.348 --> 00:25:17.307 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
L-e-o

491
00:25:17.391 --> 00:25:18.434 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
s-a.

492
00:25:19.059 --> 00:25:20.436 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Occupation?

493
00:25:20.518 --> 00:25:22.271 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dabo girl.

494
00:25:22.354 --> 00:25:23.897 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Paris]
Dabo?

495
00:25:23.981 --> 00:25:25.441 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's a Ferengi game.

496
00:25:25.523 --> 00:25:27.735 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I work aboard
one of their casino ships.

497
00:25:27.818 --> 00:25:30.154 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You-- You told me
you were a teacher.

498
00:25:31.155 --> 00:25:32.197 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is this true?

499
00:25:33.531 --> 00:25:35.659 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sometimes I'm a teacher.

500
00:25:35.743 --> 00:25:38.704 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sometimes I'm a Bajoran vedek.
[laughs]

501
00:25:38.787 --> 00:25:40.581 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Whatever the customer wants.

502
00:25:40.664 --> 00:25:42.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Lieutenant Barclay tells me
that the two of you

503
00:25:43.042 --> 00:25:45.711 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
have spent a significant amount
of time together.

504
00:25:46.462 --> 00:25:48.756 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Did he ever discuss his work
at Pathfinder with you?

505
00:25:48.839 --> 00:25:51.508 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh. Wouldn't talk about
anything else.

506
00:25:51.592 --> 00:25:56.597 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It was always holograms this
and cyclic pulsars that.

507
00:25:57.306 --> 00:25:59.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And who did you share
that information with?

508
00:26:00.392 --> 00:26:01.685 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nobody.

509
00:26:02.686 --> 00:26:03.896 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I have a theory.

510
00:26:05.272 --> 00:26:06.690 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Would you like to hear it?

511
00:26:08.025 --> 00:26:09.651 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why not?

512
00:26:09.735 --> 00:26:11.779 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think that some
of your Ferengi friends

513
00:26:11.862 --> 00:26:14.448 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
found a way to profit
from Lieutenant Barclay's work.

514
00:26:15.616 --> 00:26:17.785 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think you were encouraged

515
00:26:17.868 --> 00:26:19.453 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to get close to him,

516
00:26:19.536 --> 00:26:22.998 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and when you had all
the information you needed,

517
00:26:23.082 --> 00:26:24.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
you left him.

518
00:26:24.582 --> 00:26:28.170 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I left Reg
for one simple reason.

519
00:26:29.046 --> 00:26:30.214 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's boring.

520
00:26:33.050 --> 00:26:35.969 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[door opens, closes]

521
00:26:37.012 --> 00:26:38.806 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't tell me you never noticed.

522
00:26:40.933 --> 00:26:42.684 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
With the Admiral's permission,

523
00:26:42.768 --> 00:26:44.853 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'd like a moment alone
with Leosa.

524
00:26:46.396 --> 00:26:49.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't think therapy is what
this woman needs, Counselor.

525
00:26:49.483 --> 00:26:51.318 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Five minutes, Admiral.

526
00:26:52.778 --> 00:26:54.696 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Five minutes.

527
00:26:57.199 --> 00:26:58.242 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[door opens]

528
00:27:00.577 --> 00:27:03.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[door closes]

529
00:27:13.006 --> 00:27:14.800 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Did you know
I'm a Betazoid?

530
00:27:14.883 --> 00:27:16.468 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm empathic,

531
00:27:16.552 --> 00:27:20.139 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
which means I know
when people are lying.

532
00:27:21.390 --> 00:27:25.435 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Tell me, what's the longest
you've ever been incarcerated?

533
00:27:25.519 --> 00:27:27.896 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughs]

534
00:27:27.980 --> 00:27:30.899 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You can't send me
to prison, Counselor.

535
00:27:30.983 --> 00:27:32.734 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I didn't do anything wrong.

536
00:27:33.569 --> 00:27:38.740 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe not, but I can order you
held for psychiatric observation.

537
00:27:39.700 --> 00:27:41.869 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Extended observation.

538
00:27:43.412 --> 00:27:47.332 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I may not be a Betazoid
but I work a dabo table,

539
00:27:47.416 --> 00:27:50.878 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and I know
when somebody's bluffing.

540
00:27:54.506 --> 00:27:56.258 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Try me.

541
00:28:05.142 --> 00:28:06.518 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You were correct, Admiral.

542
00:28:06.602 --> 00:28:10.189 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Ferengi did steal
Reg's hologram-- twice.

543
00:28:10.898 --> 00:28:12.941 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is the ship
you need to look for.

544
00:28:23.160 --> 00:28:24.203 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Leosa]
That's it.

545
00:28:25.871 --> 00:28:27.080 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's Nunk's ship.

546
00:28:30.125 --> 00:28:33.754 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- Nunk?
- My... employer.

547
00:28:34.671 --> 00:28:36.423 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Scans indicate they've been
in the vicinity

548
00:28:36.506 --> 00:28:38.967 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
of that star
for the last 43 hours.

549
00:28:39.051 --> 00:28:40.093 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why?

550
00:28:41.178 --> 00:28:42.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't know.

551
00:28:42.930 --> 00:28:44.556 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She's telling
the truth...

552
00:28:44.640 --> 00:28:45.974 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
for once.

553
00:28:46.058 --> 00:28:48.060 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Ferengi wouldn't
have stolen the hologram

554
00:28:48.143 --> 00:28:50.103 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
if they didn't think
it was valuable.

555
00:28:50.187 --> 00:28:53.106 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They're probably waiting
to rendezvous with a buyer.

556
00:28:54.107 --> 00:28:56.193 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are there any Starfleet ships
in that area?

557
00:28:56.276 --> 00:28:58.403 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Carolina is
.7 light-years away.

558
00:28:58.487 --> 00:29:00.822 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
At maximum warp,
it could reach them in two hours.

559
00:29:00.906 --> 00:29:02.616 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Open a channel.

560
00:29:04.618 --> 00:29:07.037 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Computer, open a secure channel
to the Carolina.

561
00:29:07.537 --> 00:29:11.124 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Paris] Tell Captain Peterson
to adjust his course immediately.

562
00:29:13.919 --> 00:29:17.172 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Was everything that happened
between us a lie?

563
00:29:18.632 --> 00:29:20.050 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not everything.

564
00:29:20.133 --> 00:29:22.594 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just the parts where I expressed
affection for you.

565
00:29:22.678 --> 00:29:23.720 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groans]

566
00:29:25.097 --> 00:29:26.139 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh...

567
00:29:27.015 --> 00:29:30.811 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
if it makes any difference,
it wasn't personal.

568
00:29:30.894 --> 00:29:32.938 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It was just... business.

569
00:29:33.605 --> 00:29:37.150 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What exactly is a broken heart
worth these days, hmm?

570
00:29:39.361 --> 00:29:40.779 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ten percent.

571
00:29:41.488 --> 00:29:42.906 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of what?

572
00:29:42.990 --> 00:29:45.033 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Profits from
the nanoprobes.

573
00:29:46.159 --> 00:29:47.661 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- Nanoprobes?
- Mm-hmm.

574
00:29:47.744 --> 00:29:50.038 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- Borg nanoprobes?
- Yeah.

575
00:29:50.122 --> 00:29:54.126 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Gegis says they're worth
two billion times their weight in latinum.

576
00:29:54.209 --> 00:29:55.460 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh.

577
00:30:02.968 --> 00:30:05.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't think I quite understand
the problem, Doctor.

578
00:30:05.721 --> 00:30:08.807 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are you aware that he's been
doing impressions of you?

579
00:30:08.890 --> 00:30:10.976 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You should hear
his Tuvok-- it's eerie.

580
00:30:11.059 --> 00:30:12.102 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's disrespectful.

581
00:30:12.185 --> 00:30:13.854 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What do you want me
to do, deactivate him?

582
00:30:13.937 --> 00:30:16.189 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just long enough to run
a diagnostic of his program.

583
00:30:16.273 --> 00:30:19.151 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
His recent behavior may be indicative
of a more serious problem.

584
00:30:19.234 --> 00:30:20.861 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I haven't seen
any evidence of that.

585
00:30:20.944 --> 00:30:24.197 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Of course not.
In front of you, he's all smiles,

586
00:30:24.281 --> 00:30:29.077 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I've seen him be...
rude and careless,

587
00:30:29.161 --> 00:30:31.580 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
two traits the real
Lieutenant Barclay never exhibited.

588
00:30:31.663 --> 00:30:34.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I know the real Barclay
is a friend of yours,

589
00:30:34.541 --> 00:30:36.418 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and I'm sorry
if the holographic version

590
00:30:36.501 --> 00:30:37.961 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
hasn't lived up
to your expectations,

591
00:30:38.045 --> 00:30:40.339 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but that's hardly reason
to deactivate him.

592
00:30:40.422 --> 00:30:43.258 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are the lives of 150 crewmen
reason enough?

593
00:30:43.800 --> 00:30:44.634 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe you're right.

594
00:30:44.718 --> 00:30:46.261 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe I am overreacting,

595
00:30:47.012 --> 00:30:48.263 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but what if I'm right?

596
00:30:50.057 --> 00:30:53.060 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're less than a light-year away
from the geodesic fold.

597
00:30:54.394 --> 00:30:56.605 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you want to risk
being led through it

598
00:30:56.688 --> 00:30:59.107 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
by a malfunctioning hologram?

599
00:31:01.401 --> 00:31:03.236 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain, you saved us
a com call.

600
00:31:03.320 --> 00:31:05.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're ready to bring the
enhanced shielding on line.

601
00:31:05.572 --> 00:31:08.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Good work.
I need a moment alone with Reg.

602
00:31:09.910 --> 00:31:11.661 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your program has been
running continuously

603
00:31:11.745 --> 00:31:13.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
for how many hours now?

604
00:31:13.497 --> 00:31:15.874 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
56 hours, 11 minutes
and 21 seconds.

605
00:31:15.957 --> 00:31:18.418 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'd like to run
a diagnostic of your matrix,

606
00:31:18.502 --> 00:31:20.295 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
make sure you haven't
suffered any degradation

607
00:31:20.379 --> 00:31:21.880 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
over the last few days.

608
00:31:23.131 --> 00:31:24.883 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This isn't the, uh...

609
00:31:24.966 --> 00:31:26.551 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Doctor's idea, is it?

610
00:31:28.011 --> 00:31:30.597 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He expressed some concern
for your well-being, yes.

611
00:31:30.680 --> 00:31:31.973 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I bet he did.

612
00:31:32.057 --> 00:31:35.519 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Believe me, Reg, the crew and I
are grateful for everything you've done,

613
00:31:35.602 --> 00:31:37.479 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but we need to take
every precaution.

614
00:31:37.562 --> 00:31:38.605 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I understand perfectly.

615
00:31:38.688 --> 00:31:40.148 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And if the ship's Doctor thinks

616
00:31:40.232 --> 00:31:43.068 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I need a checkup,
who am I to argue?

617
00:32:03.171 --> 00:32:05.132 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why are you hiding
in the corner?

618
00:32:05.215 --> 00:32:06.508 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not hiding.

619
00:32:07.134 --> 00:32:10.971 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm working on a way
to foil the Ferengi's plans.

620
00:32:11.054 --> 00:32:13.056 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Reg, there's nothing
left to foil.

621
00:32:13.140 --> 00:32:15.976 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Carolina will have them
in custody within the hour.

622
00:32:16.059 --> 00:32:17.811 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Leosa said the Ferengi

623
00:32:17.894 --> 00:32:20.522 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
were going to be selling
Borg nanoprobes.

624
00:32:21.481 --> 00:32:24.234 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What does that have to do
with Voyager?

625
00:32:24.317 --> 00:32:26.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They have a Borg crewman.

626
00:32:26.194 --> 00:32:27.737 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Think about it.

627
00:32:27.821 --> 00:32:31.366 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Ferengi stole the original
Barclay hologram a month ago.

628
00:32:31.450 --> 00:32:34.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That gave them time
to reprogram it

629
00:32:34.369 --> 00:32:36.913 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and then smuggle it to Voyager
in the next transmission.

630
00:32:36.997 --> 00:32:38.707 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Reprogram it to do what?

631
00:32:38.790 --> 00:32:41.960 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Steal Seven of Nine's
nanoprobes.

632
00:32:42.878 --> 00:32:46.506 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
For all we know, he could be
dissecting her right now.

633
00:32:47.883 --> 00:32:51.845 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What would the Ferengi want
with assimilation technology?

634
00:32:51.928 --> 00:32:54.473 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, nanoprobes
aren't just for assimilating.

635
00:32:54.556 --> 00:32:57.017 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They can reanimate
necrotic tissue,

636
00:32:57.100 --> 00:32:58.602 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
slow down the aging process.

637
00:32:58.685 --> 00:33:01.021 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They'd be priceless
for the Ferengi.

638
00:33:01.771 --> 00:33:04.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Reg, even if the Ferengi

639
00:33:04.483 --> 00:33:08.487 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
did reprogram your hologram
to steal the nanoprobes,

640
00:33:08.570 --> 00:33:10.989 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
how would they get
their hands on them?

641
00:33:11.072 --> 00:33:13.700 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Voyager's
30,000 light-years away.

642
00:33:14.784 --> 00:33:16.453 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I haven't figured
that part out yet.

643
00:33:16.536 --> 00:33:21.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe they discovered a--
a wormhole or a subspace corridor.

644
00:33:24.002 --> 00:33:26.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Have you mentioned any of this
to Commander Harkins?

645
00:33:26.630 --> 00:33:28.507 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not yet. I can't.

646
00:33:29.591 --> 00:33:31.343 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If I don't bring him
hard evidence,

647
00:33:31.426 --> 00:33:33.220 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
he'll just think
that I'm fantasizing.

648
00:33:35.597 --> 00:33:39.726 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
For the time being, we need
to keep this between us.

649
00:33:48.235 --> 00:33:49.277 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That tickles, Lieutenant.

650
00:33:50.278 --> 00:33:52.447 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sorry, Reg,
we're almost finished.

651
00:33:53.198 --> 00:33:55.408 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Have you identified
any problems yet?

652
00:33:55.492 --> 00:33:57.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've gone over
his entire matrix.

653
00:33:57.202 --> 00:33:58.662 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's working perfectly.

654
00:33:58.745 --> 00:34:02.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe I'm not the one
who needs a diagnostic, hmm?

655
00:34:03.792 --> 00:34:06.461 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm a big enough hologram
to admit when I'm wrong.

656
00:34:06.545 --> 00:34:07.837 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sorry I doubted you.

657
00:34:07.921 --> 00:34:10.507 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, if anyone is owed
an apology, it's you.

658
00:34:10.590 --> 00:34:12.092 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I should've been more sensitive.

659
00:34:12.175 --> 00:34:13.468 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Friends?

660
00:34:14.386 --> 00:34:15.428 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Friends.

661
00:34:15.512 --> 00:34:16.972 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now that that's
out of the way, Captain,

662
00:34:17.055 --> 00:34:19.266 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
what do you say we get
this ship back to Earth?

663
00:34:24.938 --> 00:34:26.398 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeping]

664
00:34:26.481 --> 00:34:27.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's time.

665
00:34:27.816 --> 00:34:30.527 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Initiate the geodesic pulse.

666
00:34:44.833 --> 00:34:47.544 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Admiral Paris] Would someone care
to tell me what that is?

667
00:34:55.760 --> 00:34:58.388 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's a geodesic fold, Admiral.

668
00:34:58.471 --> 00:35:00.807 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's how they're going
to get the nanoprobes.

669
00:35:03.893 --> 00:35:06.688 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Two million kilometers
and closing, Captain.

670
00:35:06.771 --> 00:35:08.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Take us to
one-quarter impulse.

671
00:35:08.815 --> 00:35:10.191 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Bridge to Astrometrics.

672
00:35:10.275 --> 00:35:12.736 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Bring the enhanced
shielding on line.

673
00:35:12.819 --> 00:35:13.820 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Aye, Commander.

674
00:35:13.903 --> 00:35:14.946 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[alarm sounds]

675
00:35:15.030 --> 00:35:16.364 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's wrong?

676
00:35:19.284 --> 00:35:22.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The fold contains three radiation types
we didn't account for.

677
00:35:23.246 --> 00:35:25.165 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The shield modifications
are not enough.

678
00:35:25.248 --> 00:35:26.374 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, the shields
were modified

679
00:35:26.458 --> 00:35:28.084 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to work in combination
with the inoculations.

680
00:35:28.168 --> 00:35:29.210 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We'll be fine.

681
00:35:29.294 --> 00:35:31.796 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If the shields fail,
the inoculations will be irrelevant.

682
00:35:31.880 --> 00:35:33.840 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- Astrometrics to the Bridge.
- [Janeway] <i>Go ahead.</i>

683
00:35:33.923 --> 00:35:36.009 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[electrical crackling]

684
00:35:39.054 --> 00:35:40.263 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>What is it, Seven?</i>

685
00:35:41.181 --> 00:35:43.266 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Seven's voice]
There was a problem, Captain,

686
00:35:43.350 --> 00:35:44.559 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but I've corrected it.

687
00:35:46.394 --> 00:35:47.479 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeping]

688
00:35:53.652 --> 00:35:57.238 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm using the MIDAS Array to tap
into the Ferengi ship's sensors.

689
00:35:57.322 --> 00:35:59.115 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They're receiving telemetry
through the fold.

690
00:35:59.199 --> 00:36:01.910 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If I'm reading this correctly,
Voyager's headed right for it.

691
00:36:01.993 --> 00:36:03.370 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Captain Janeway knows better

692
00:36:03.453 --> 00:36:05.705 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
than to take her ship
into such a dangerous anomaly.

693
00:36:05.789 --> 00:36:09.459 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If the Ferengi did alter
my hologram, then...

694
00:36:09.542 --> 00:36:13.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
it might... might be possible
for him to have taken over the ship.

695
00:36:13.588 --> 00:36:15.715 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
One hologram
against an entire crew?

696
00:36:15.799 --> 00:36:18.093 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He may have found a way
to incapacitate the crew

697
00:36:18.176 --> 00:36:19.761 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
or to commandeer
the ship's systems,

698
00:36:19.844 --> 00:36:23.264 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but either way, we've got to get
the Carolina to close the fold.

699
00:36:23.348 --> 00:36:25.225 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Carolina isn't
equipped to do that.

700
00:36:25.308 --> 00:36:27.852 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then they'll have to commandeer
the Ferengi ship and do it from there.

701
00:36:27.936 --> 00:36:29.521 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Carolina's still
half a light-year away.

702
00:36:29.604 --> 00:36:31.272 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They won't make it in time.

703
00:36:31.356 --> 00:36:34.401 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Can we transmit a message,
warn Voyager?

704
00:36:35.485 --> 00:36:37.320 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Not through
a geodesic fold.

705
00:36:44.536 --> 00:36:48.456 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Our own starship,
with multiphasic shielding

706
00:36:48.540 --> 00:36:52.043 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and a gold-pressed
latinum hull.

707
00:36:52.127 --> 00:36:55.296 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We'll have enough left over
to buy a fleet of casino ships!

708
00:36:55.380 --> 00:36:58.967 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I have a better idea--
lobe enlargements!

709
00:37:00.218 --> 00:37:01.970 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- [console beeping]
- Shh!

710
00:37:02.053 --> 00:37:03.722 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Ooh, someone's
hailing us.

711
00:37:03.805 --> 00:37:04.848 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who?

712
00:37:04.931 --> 00:37:07.434 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can't tell.
There's too much interference.

713
00:37:07.517 --> 00:37:08.893 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Answer it.

714
00:37:11.730 --> 00:37:13.565 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's the hologram.

715
00:37:13.648 --> 00:37:16.276 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You said it was impossible
to communicate through the fold.

716
00:37:16.359 --> 00:37:17.569 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I thought it was.

717
00:37:18.319 --> 00:37:20.029 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I guess I did a better job

718
00:37:20.113 --> 00:37:22.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
of reprogramming the hologram
than I thought.

719
00:37:22.240 --> 00:37:23.408 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>[static]</i>

720
00:37:23.491 --> 00:37:27.495 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We must close
the geodesic fold immediately.

721
00:37:27.579 --> 00:37:30.540 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Captain Janeway</i>
<i>has found out about our plan.</i>

722
00:37:30.623 --> 00:37:32.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If that's true,

723
00:37:32.417 --> 00:37:34.502 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
then why is she still
headed for the fold?

724
00:37:35.086 --> 00:37:36.588 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Because she...

725
00:37:38.173 --> 00:37:39.966 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
found a way
to protect her ship.

726
00:37:40.049 --> 00:37:41.176 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Impossible.

727
00:37:41.259 --> 00:37:42.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You don't know Janeway.

728
00:37:43.178 --> 00:37:45.805 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She's uncanny
when it comes to shields.

729
00:37:45.889 --> 00:37:46.931 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She's furious.

730
00:37:47.974 --> 00:37:51.728 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She said she was going to kill
whoever tried to harm her crew.

731
00:37:51.811 --> 00:37:54.898 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I strongly suggest
you abort the mission.

732
00:37:56.024 --> 00:37:57.233 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What should we do?

733
00:37:58.401 --> 00:38:00.487 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Go to warp before Janeway
makes it through.

734
00:38:00.570 --> 00:38:01.780 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>No, you mustn't!</i>

735
00:38:01.863 --> 00:38:04.282 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Voyager has Borg interquadrental

736
00:38:04.365 --> 00:38:08.661 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
warp drives and...
Hirogen hunting sensors

737
00:38:08.745 --> 00:38:10.288 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and Vidiian phase torpedoes.

738
00:38:10.371 --> 00:38:13.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No matter where you run,
Voyager will find you.

739
00:38:13.792 --> 00:38:18.213 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your only hope...
is to close the fold.

740
00:38:27.722 --> 00:38:29.432 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Harkins to Holodeck 1.

741
00:38:29.516 --> 00:38:31.142 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Barclay]
<i>Go ahead, Pete.</i>

742
00:38:31.226 --> 00:38:32.811 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It worked, Reg.

743
00:38:32.894 --> 00:38:34.562 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>They've started</i>
<i>to close the fold.</i>

744
00:38:34.646 --> 00:38:36.439 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[sighs]
Computer, end program.

745
00:38:39.651 --> 00:38:40.693 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>[console beeping]</i>

746
00:38:41.402 --> 00:38:42.445 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Something's wrong, Captain.

747
00:38:43.321 --> 00:38:44.823 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Barclay]
<i>Astrometrics to the Bridge.</i>

748
00:38:44.906 --> 00:38:46.115 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Why are we stopping?</i>

749
00:38:47.116 --> 00:38:48.660 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The fold's collapsing, Reg.

750
00:38:48.743 --> 00:38:50.411 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>We didn't make it in time.</i>

751
00:38:50.495 --> 00:38:52.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's not too late
if we remodulate the shields.

752
00:38:52.747 --> 00:38:55.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I appreciate your determination,
but we can't risk it.

753
00:38:55.416 --> 00:38:57.001 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You did everything you could.

754
00:38:57.085 --> 00:38:58.127 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>[console beeping]</i>

755
00:38:59.254 --> 00:39:02.507 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain, someone just initiated
a site-to-site transport.

756
00:39:02.590 --> 00:39:03.883 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who?

757
00:39:03.967 --> 00:39:05.009 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Seven and Reg.

758
00:39:05.093 --> 00:39:06.553 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They've beamed
to an escape pod.

759
00:39:06.636 --> 00:39:08.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Bridge to Seven of Nine.
What's going on?

760
00:39:12.684 --> 00:39:13.726 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The pod's been launched.

761
00:39:13.810 --> 00:39:15.228 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Put a tractor beam on it.

762
00:39:17.939 --> 00:39:19.941 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There is too much interference
from the fold.

763
00:39:20.024 --> 00:39:21.860 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Harry, can you get
a transporter lock?

764
00:39:23.945 --> 00:39:25.196 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeping]

765
00:39:25.280 --> 00:39:26.322 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What now?

766
00:39:26.865 --> 00:39:28.533 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's something
coming through the fold.

767
00:39:28.616 --> 00:39:31.035 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- Voyager?
- No, it's too small.

768
00:39:31.119 --> 00:39:32.287 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A phase torpedo!

769
00:39:32.996 --> 00:39:35.707 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Raise shields!
Brace for impact!

770
00:39:38.126 --> 00:39:40.044 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[muffled crash]

771
00:39:42.297 --> 00:39:43.923 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's an escape pod.

772
00:39:49.679 --> 00:39:53.474 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe the hologram
sent us the drone.

773
00:39:53.558 --> 00:39:55.059 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ooh...!

774
00:39:55.143 --> 00:39:56.686 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Check what's in there.

775
00:39:59.314 --> 00:40:00.523 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nothing.

776
00:40:01.524 --> 00:40:05.445 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No Borg corpse,
no nanoprobes.

777
00:40:06.195 --> 00:40:07.822 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No profit.

778
00:40:09.365 --> 00:40:11.117 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[all sigh]

779
00:40:11.200 --> 00:40:13.620 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Captain's Log, supplemental.</i>

780
00:40:13.703 --> 00:40:15.747 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Seven of Nine has recovered</i>
<i>from her injuries</i>

781
00:40:15.830 --> 00:40:18.082 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>and "Reg" has been deactivated.</i>

782
00:40:18.166 --> 00:40:20.543 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Until we finish</i>
<i>analyzing his program,</i>

783
00:40:20.627 --> 00:40:22.754 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>his motivations</i>
<i>remain a mystery.</i>

784
00:40:30.053 --> 00:40:33.056 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Making first contact
with a new life-form?

785
00:40:33.139 --> 00:40:34.182 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Mom's apple pie."

786
00:40:35.224 --> 00:40:38.061 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Neelix thought a little home cooking
might cheer me up.

787
00:40:38.144 --> 00:40:38.978 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And...?

788
00:40:39.062 --> 00:40:42.148 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I haven't worked up the courage
to taste it yet.

789
00:40:42.231 --> 00:40:44.442 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Have you figured out
what went wrong with Reg?

790
00:40:44.525 --> 00:40:48.029 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, Seven thinks our proximity
to the fold degraded his matrix,

791
00:40:48.112 --> 00:40:51.491 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but if you ask me, it was
a recursive error in his logic subroutine.

792
00:40:51.574 --> 00:40:53.368 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

793
00:40:58.081 --> 00:40:59.832 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not bad...

794
00:40:59.916 --> 00:41:02.418 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but it would have tasted better
in San Francisco.

795
00:41:06.339 --> 00:41:08.591 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If it'll make you
feel any better,

796
00:41:08.675 --> 00:41:10.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll let you in
on a little secret.

797
00:41:11.761 --> 00:41:13.262 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was on the Bridge
this morning

798
00:41:13.346 --> 00:41:16.265 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
when we received a hail
from an Iconian scientist.

799
00:41:16.349 --> 00:41:19.477 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He claims to have
a transdimensional gateway

800
00:41:19.560 --> 00:41:21.604 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that can take us anywhere
in the galaxy.

801
00:41:23.189 --> 00:41:24.857 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not <i>that </i>gullible.

802
00:41:24.941 --> 00:41:27.193 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's true. I was there.

803
00:41:27.276 --> 00:41:29.779 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Captain doesn't want us
to get our hopes up,

804
00:41:29.862 --> 00:41:33.074 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but personally, I think we'll
be home by the end of the week.

805
00:41:36.327 --> 00:41:37.829 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you serious?

806
00:41:37.912 --> 00:41:38.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

807
00:41:39.038 --> 00:41:40.748 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You were right about him.

808
00:41:48.673 --> 00:41:53.678 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Computer, install Barclay
Security Protocol 21-Alpha.

809
00:41:54.345 --> 00:41:56.180 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Installation complete.</i>

810
00:41:57.557 --> 00:41:59.100 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Identify yourself.

811
00:41:59.183 --> 00:42:01.853 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
C-computer, deactivate
Barclay program.

812
00:42:03.312 --> 00:42:04.522 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sorry.

813
00:42:04.605 --> 00:42:08.234 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I-- I've been programming him
with new security precautions

814
00:42:08.317 --> 00:42:10.069 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
s-so he can't be stolen again.

815
00:42:10.153 --> 00:42:11.904 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You seem to be off
to a good start.

816
00:42:11.988 --> 00:42:13.990 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thought you'd, uh,
be back at the beach.

817
00:42:14.073 --> 00:42:17.660 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Will and I decided to spend
the rest of our vacation in Tiburon.

818
00:42:17.744 --> 00:42:20.246 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We were wondering
if you're free for dinner tonight.

819
00:42:20.830 --> 00:42:22.623 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh, I, oh...

820
00:42:22.707 --> 00:42:25.460 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, I, uh, I-I wouldn't want
to be a "third nacelle."

821
00:42:25.543 --> 00:42:26.586 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not possible.

822
00:42:27.170 --> 00:42:28.963 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Will's bringing
a friend for you.

823
00:42:29.797 --> 00:42:30.840 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Her name's Maril.

824
00:42:31.758 --> 00:42:33.217 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're going to adore her.

825
00:42:33.301 --> 00:42:36.888 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'd like to,
but I-- I still have, uh...

826
00:42:36.971 --> 00:42:39.515 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
dozens of protocols to install.

827
00:42:39.599 --> 00:42:40.683 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe next time.

828
00:42:40.767 --> 00:42:43.978 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Look, Reg,
I know Leosa hurt you,

829
00:42:44.062 --> 00:42:47.190 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but hiding inside a hologrid
isn't the answer.

830
00:42:47.273 --> 00:42:50.109 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You need to get out,
meet new people.

831
00:42:50.985 --> 00:42:54.572 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This Maril wouldn't happen to be
a dabo girl by any chance?

832
00:42:55.073 --> 00:42:57.825 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She's a teacher, actually--
a real one.

833
00:42:57.909 --> 00:43:00.328 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
- Are you sure?
- Don't worry, Reg.

834
00:43:00.411 --> 00:43:03.122 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We've taken
security precautions.

